physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Physical examination notable for eunuchoid habitus, small breasts, and normal external genitalia.

physical_examinations.vital_signs: Baseline LH level: 0.3 IU/L; Baseline FSH level: 0.5 IU/L; PRL level: 1.8 ng/mL; Estradiol level: less than 20 pg/mL.
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Peak LH level of 1.3 IU/L at 30 min and a peak FSH level of 1.6 IU/L at 120 min after the GnRH bolus.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Initial response to a single bolus of GnRH was markedly diminished, but followed by multiple cycles with varying responses to different GnRH doses.
